    "description": "<blockquote><p><strong>Requirements:</strong> you must have mastered the <strong>Illusionist</strong> Class.</p></blockquote><p><span>You learn the ultimate <strong>Illusionist</strong> spell: </span><strong>Create Phantasm: Numen</strong><span>.</span></p><table style=\"width:96.2791%\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width:15.3584%\"><col style=\"width:12.9693%\"><col style=\"width:27.3038%\"><col style=\"width:44.3686%\"></colgroup><tbody><tr><td style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Create Phantasm: Numen</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>MP:</strong> 50</td><td style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Target:</strong> Special</td><td style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Duration:</strong> Instantaneous</td></tr></tbody></table><p>You can now have up to <strong>4</strong> active Phantasms, but one of them must necessarily be <strong>Numen</strong>. Also, you cannot have more than one Numen Phantasm active at a time. This Phantasm cannot be used in any of the Illusionist's Skills or Spells.</p><p>Numen is bound by the same set of special rules as any other Phantasm, with the following exceptions:</p><ul><li><p>Numen Phantasms cost 50 MP to cast.</p></li><li><p>Numen's Phantasmal Vitality equals <strong>twice your base Insight die size plus your level</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Once active, <strong>Numen has its own turn and a single action</strong>. It does not benefit from Spells that grant additional actions. Numen’s turn can be taken either before or after the <strong>Illusionist’s</strong> turn.</p></li></ul><p>When creating a Numen Phantasm, choose one essence, which dictates Numen's Damage Type:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p style=\"text-align: center;\">Numem</p></td><td><p style=\"text-align: center;\">Damage type</p></td></tr><tr><td><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Ravana</strong></p></td><td><p style=\"text-align: center;\">Physical @ICON[physical]</p></td></tr><tr><td><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Asura</strong></p></td><td><p style=\"text-align: center;\">Light @ICON[light]</p></td></tr><tr><td><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Diablos</strong></p></td><td><p style=\"text-align: center;\">Dark @ICON[dark]</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>The target hit by Numen suﬀers <strong>【HR + 14】</strong> damage.</p><p>This damage increases to 18 if you are level 20 or higher, or to 20 if you are level 40 or higher.</p><p>Damage dealt by Numen ignores Resistances and Immunities.</p><p>The range of the attack is determined by your current weapon.</p>",
